<DOC><DOCNO> DOE1-85-0067 </DOCNO><TEXT>In the application of geothermal water, melts especially such as silicadeposit to form hard scales in transport tubes and pipes which sometimesbe a cause of blocking of injection wells. This invention is to inhibitthe production of silica scales by mere addition of medicaments to asystem of water to be treated, with no requirement for PH adjustmentof the water, sedimentation treatment, etc. The medicaments are N-laurylpyridinium chloride, N-stearyle pyridinium chloride, N-stearyle picaliniumchloride, N-lauryl picolinium chloride, N-layryl picolinium iodide, etc.The application is only to add 0.01-1000 mg/l of them to the water tobe treated. (1 tab)</TEXT></DOC>